body:
@iphydf wrote:

> problem: the tox public interface defines a lot of enumerations that are duplicated in the implementation

Proposed solutions:
- let directly include tox.h (carefully checking that only enums/types are used from there)
- split tox.h into two files: one for enums/types, one for functions

comment_data.body: Let's go with solution 1 and later maybe move to solution 2. We can keep a TODO in tox.h to make sure that in the new apidsl we generate a tox.enums.h (or .constants.h) containing only the enums/#defines.

rename.to: Deduplicate enums and typedefs from tox.h and lower layers

title: Deduplicate enums and typedefs from tox.h and lower layers
